7/ It wouldn't be a CCLA event without the blessings of some of the Cool Cat OG's ... for this we called @evanluza the creative director and secret weapon for the Cool Cats! After meeting him at the event ... this piece of work is so fitting! Looks rare! https://t.co/IdrHeRFrl5

6/ @foodmasku the man, the myth, the legend. This artist has been one of the top artist in the NFT space for as long as we can remember! The amazing pieces he creates are unique and delectable. He's always cooking something amazing up for his collectors! https://t.co/Fa6Ujox4vq

5/ @VinnieHager had just sold out of his Letters collection and also had some time to create a 1/1 Cool Cat inspired rendition of his awesome artwork! The lines and designs that he comes up with are something out of this world! https://t.co/iJEQiCSwvS

4/ @CakeNygard is the first artist we called up, he's been very involved in the NFT community from early on and has a very unique style to his work! We love the psychedelic technique he uses to create this! This 1/1 piece is something special. $MILK Monsta https://t.co/uNekiifMiw

3/ An auction that we host. 50% goes back to the artist, 40% goes to the local charity and 10% goes back to CCLA to help fund the event and future events. The NY organization we are donating to will be @NYCares they work with volunteers to help underprivileged youths in NYC

2/ A big part of why we do these meet up's is also to highlight some of the artist that are within our @coolcatsnft community and together we help raise some money for local charities and organizations that need a little extra help from us! We ask the artist to create 1/1's for..

1/ GM world! The NFT NYC event on Tuesday was one for the history books! There was a line around the corner in the middle of Times Square for the unofficial @coolcatsnft meet up! CCNYC had over 750 RSVP's for this event, that is about 500 people more than CCLA!!!
